Our client, a multinational engineering company, global leader in engineering solutions, is seeking a Legal Contract Engineer, for the VIII region.

Responsabilities:
•	To interpret and explain contractual clauses;
•	To provide the certification required by contract for signature by the contractual representatives;
•	To check that contractual obligations are absolved by Employer and Subcontractors;
•	To check the expected final cost estimates against budget values;
•	To check Subcontractors’ Work Progress Status sheets prior to approval by the Site Manager;
•	To prepare for the Site Manager’s signature the Works Progress Status sheets for presentation to Employer;
•	Together with the Supervisors, to discuss and where possible reach an agreement with the Subcontractor concerning new prices, contractual amendments and claims, preparing the supporting documents for formal issue by Home Office Subcontracts Unit (APPAL);
•	To prepare, in collaboration with the Construction Manager, for the Site Manager’s signature, the Field change orders and claims to be dispatched to Employer;
•	To prepare the documents for the award of local subcontracts;
•	To prepare his own section of the construction monthly progress report.

We offer:
•	To join an important world leader multinational corporation.
•	Career development and professional projections.
•	Interesting salary.

BVM Consultores invites you to send your resumee to our e-mail contract.engineer@bvmconsultores.cl or to apply in our web site, www.serecluta.com

